to him on a silver platter.

13:30.643 --> 13:31.906
Yeah, but the thing is...

13:32.011 --> 13:33.445
you and me, Red,
we're different.

13:33.546 --> 13:34.672
See, we're doers.

13:34.781 --> 13:35.805
We're doers.

13:35.915 --> 13:36.973
Yeah.

13:37.083 --> 13:38.312
Yeah, we are.

13:38.418 --> 13:40.785
But does that mean we have
to accept every challenge?

13:40.887 --> 13:43.549
No, I'm a very flexible person.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.590
You know, when I was
shooting over that ramp,

13:45.692 --> 13:47.353
flying over that shark,

13:47.460 --> 13:49.519
something my grandfather said
came right back to me.

13:49.629 --> 13:50.926
Yeah, you should remember it,

13:51.030 --> 13:52.225
climbing up that ladder
to stardom.

13:52.332 --> 13:53.299
What?

13:53.400 --> 13:55.300
He said life is filled
with challenges.

13:55.402 --> 13:56.699
You take 'em all.

13:56.803 --> 13:58.168
Except those that are gonna
break your neck.

13:58.271 --> 13:59.261
(chuckles)

13:59.372 --> 14:00.498
Course, he said it in Italian.

14:00.607 --> 14:02.234
(laughs)

14:02.342 --> 14:05.573
So you knew all the time that
you were gonna make it, huh?

14:05.678 --> 14:07.578
Yeah, I did.

14:07.680 --> 14:08.943
Well...

14:09.048 --> 14:11.517
deep down, I... I knew
you were gonna make it, too.

14:11.618 --> 14:13.746
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.218
I wasn't sure the shark knew.

14:15.321 --> 14:16.618
The shark?!

14:16.723 --> 14:19.090
(both chuckle)

14:19.192 --> 14:21.354
<i>RICHIE: You know,
signing a <i>movie contract</i></i>

14:21.461 --> 14:24.123
is almost as scary
as jumping over a shark.

14:24.230 --> 14:26.221
Oh, man.

14:26.332 --> 14:28.323
$200 a week, that's...

14:28.435 --> 14:29.664
that's really a lot of money.

14:29.769 --> 14:30.964
JOANIE:
Oh, wow.

14:31.070 --> 14:34.836
50 new Big Bopper albums
every seven days.

14:34.941 --> 14:36.636
And that's just for openers.

14:36.743 --> 14:38.768
Yeah, but it's
a five-year contract.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.437
That's five years
out of my life.

14:40.547 --> 14:42.572
Howard, if Richard
signs the contract,

14:42.682 --> 14:44.548
would we all move to Hollywood?

14:44.651 --> 14:46.415
Well, I think he's
perfectly capable

14:46.519 --> 14:48.317
of living out here
alone, sweetheart.

14:48.421 --> 14:51.049
Well, to play it safe,
better send me with him.

14:52.358 --> 14:53.587
Nice try.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.094
It's a five-year contract...

14:57.197 --> 14:58.892
and there's no guarantee
of-of success,

14:58.998 --> 15:00.090
let alone being a star.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.361
I know.

15:01.468 --> 15:03.527
You throw your dice
and you take your chance.

15:03.636 --> 15:05.798
Go, stay. What's the big deal?

15:05.905 --> 15:07.896
Mom and Dad'll always have me.

15:09.042 --> 15:10.339
Go to your room.

15:10.443 --> 15:12.707
My room is your room, Dad.

15:12.812 --> 15:14.576
Well, then go to the beach.

15:14.681 --> 15:15.705
Sent to the beach.

15:15.815 --> 15:17.078
I love California!

15:18.251 --> 15:20.447
But you stay away from
that Sandy character

15:20.553 --> 15:22.214
and all those muscle men.

15:22.322 --> 15:24.313
Oh, Dad.

15:24.424 --> 15:26.825
Well...

15:26.926 --> 15:28.087
Yes, Mom?

15:28.194 --> 15:31.630
I love you and I think
that you will be a star

15:31.731 --> 15:33.859
at whatever you do.

15:33.967 --> 15:36.800
I picked one winner
and I can pick another.

15:36.903 --> 15:39.167
Mm-hmm. Thank you, sweetheart.

15:39.272 --> 15:41.240
Just for that, you can
go to the gift shop

15:41.341 --> 15:44.641
and buy that slice of driftwood
that you wanted.

15:44.744 --> 15:46.872
- Thank you, Howard.
- Mm-hmm.

15:46.980 --> 15:48.971
I'll go get your wallet.

15:51.518 --> 15:54.613
Your mother wants me to make
a lamp out of that driftwood.

15:54.721 --> 15:56.951
I don't know how to make a lamp.

15:57.056 --> 15:59.286
I could never get the wire
in the socket

15:59.392 --> 16:00.951
that goes into the lamp.

16:01.060 --> 16:03.051
I also can't get the wire
into the plug

16:03.162 --> 16:04.789
that goes at the other end...

16:04.898 --> 16:06.593
You don't want to
hear this, do you?

16:06.699 --> 16:08.098
Well, it's just, uh...

16:08.201 --> 16:09.999
Yeah, you're a little worried
about this, aren't you?

16:10.103 --> 16:11.468
I sure am.

16:11.571 --> 16:15.235
Well, I'm sorry, Richard,
I guess I just got carried away.

16:15.341 --> 16:18.276
You know, a movie contract
and everything.

16:18.378 --> 16:19.641
You see, your mother and I

16:19.746 --> 16:22.306
always planned for you
to go to college.

16:22.415 --> 16:24.247
In fact,
you're already registered.

16:24.350 --> 16:26.512
So you think I should forget
about this and just, uh...

16:26.619 --> 16:27.609
just go to school?

16:27.720 --> 16:28.915
Well, now, I didn't say that.

16:29.022 --> 16:31.013
After all, a Hollywood contract
is very exciting.

16:31.124 --> 16:32.888
Yeah.

16:32.992 --> 16:37.327
But, uh, sometimes I wish
I was Ozzie Nelson.

16:37.430 --> 16:39.524
Then it would be easy,
because Ozzie would say,

16:39.632 --> 16:42.431
"You're going to college
and that's it."

16:42.535 --> 16:44.162
Straight out.

16:44.270 --> 16:46.170
But the best I can do for you

16:46.272 --> 16:49.242
is to just talk it outwith you.

16:49.342 --> 16:52.539
I don't think you really want me
to tell you what to do, do you?

16:53.813 --> 16:55.440
No.

16:55.548 --> 16:58.245
I guess it's my life,
and it's got to be my decision.

16:58.351 --> 17:00.911
Mm. Well, Richard...

17:02.655 --> 17:05.589
I know that whatever decision
you make, I'll be proud of you.

17:05.692 --> 17:07.319
You're my son and you've

17:07.426 --> 17:10.419
never given me cause
to be anything but proud.

17:33.319 --> 17:35.344
<i>II</i>

17:44.597 --> 17:46.588
That's your decision, huh?

17:48.534 --> 17:50.935
Yeah.

17:51.037 --> 17:52.402
200 bucks a week,

17:52.505 --> 17:54.473
that's a lot of tune-ups.

17:54.574 --> 17:57.441
Well, Fonz,

17:57.543 --> 17:59.739
being a movie star,

17:59.846 --> 18:01.473
that's not my dream.

18:01.581 --> 18:04.175
What I really want
is to be a journalist.

18:04.283 --> 18:06.274
People are gonna think
I'm bananas.

18:06.386 --> 18:07.945
Let me tell you something, Red,

18:08.054 --> 18:10.682
the important thing is you do
what you want to do,

18:10.790 --> 18:12.815
not what you think other people
think you should do.

18:12.925 --> 18:15.257
- Yeah, I know, I know.
- Hey, I'm not finished yet.

18:15.361 --> 18:18.331
Now, you got to enjoy what it is
that you're doing,

18:18.431 --> 18:21.264
because you're gonna spend
a lot of time doing it.

18:21.367 --> 18:22.835
You dig? Look at me.

18:22.935 --> 18:25.336
(Richie chuckles)

18:25.438 --> 18:27.839
Yeah, but who wouldn't want
to have all your women, Fonz?

18:27.940 --> 18:29.237
Hey, that's true,

18:29.342 --> 18:31.868
but I'm talking
about auto repair.

18:31.978 --> 18:35.209
A lot of people don't want
to get their fingernails dirty,

18:35.314 --> 18:37.248
you dig, but I love
being a mechanic,

18:37.350 --> 18:39.819
and I'm very good at it,
and that's what's cool.

18:39.919 --> 18:41.250
I see what you mean.

18:41.354 --> 18:43.686
See, I-l don't know
if I could ever act,

18:43.790 --> 18:46.191
but I know
that I can write good.

18:46.292 --> 18:47.623
No, no, no, that's "well."

18:47.727 --> 18:49.388
- Whether you could write well.
- Oh, yeah...

18:49.495 --> 18:52.089
Don't let it ever be said
that the Fonz

18:52.198 --> 18:54.098
don't talk good. Heyyy.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.669
Let's go home, Red.
Let's go home.

18:56.769 --> 18:57.964
Lead the way.

18:58.071 --> 18:59.800
I'll tell you, Fonz,

18:59.906 --> 19:01.465
this trip sure was
a great last fling

19:01.574 --> 19:02.735
before starting college.

19:02.842 --> 19:04.276
FONZIE: Yeah, next week,
you, Potsie and Ralph

19:04.377 --> 19:06.106
become collegiate types.
I like that.

19:06.212 --> 19:08.010
I like hanging out
with college men.

19:08.114 --> 19:09.513
RICHIE: You mean it's good
for your image

19:09.615 --> 19:11.777
to be with intelligent,
educated guys like us?

19:11.884 --> 19:15.047
FONZIE: No, I mean it's a great
new way to meet college chicks.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.145
(Fonzie laughing)

19:24.897 --> 19:26.387
(rock 'n' roll playing)

19:26.499 --> 19:28.991
♪ Why don't you kiss me
and you'll find out, yeah... ♪

19:31.003 --> 19:34.633
(sighs) Another day,
another dollar.

19:34.741 --> 19:37.073
You keep your money
in a coffee can, Al?

19:37.176 --> 19:39.611
Yeah, it's safe enough till
I get it home in my mattress.

19:39.712 --> 19:42.113
Oh, don't you use banks?

19:42.215 --> 19:44.081
(chuckles)
Only for change.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.548
Oh, here, I'll save you a trip.

19:45.651 --> 19:46.948
Wow.

19:47.053 --> 19:48.111
You had a good day.

19:48.221 --> 19:50.121
Oh, yeah,
between my regular clientele

19:50.223 --> 19:51.816
and the people cousin Fonzie
sends me,

19:51.924 --> 19:53.016
I do all right.

19:53.126 --> 19:54.184
Oh, that's two bucks.

19:54.293 --> 19:56.785
(chuckles)

19:56.896 --> 19:59.297
Boy, I wonder where
everybody is.

19:59.398 --> 20:01.366
Their plane landed an hour ago.

20:01.467 --> 20:03.026
Yeah, they said
they were gonna come by,

20:03.136 --> 20:04.399
but you know,
maybe it got too late

20:04.504 --> 20:05.801
and they just went on home.

20:06.873 --> 20:08.204
Oh, good night, Rosa.

20:08.307 --> 20:11.106
Yeah... good night, Rosa.

20:12.178 --> 20:14.010
Wah, wah, wah.

20:14.113 --> 20:17.640
Chachi, Chachi,
she's too old for you.

20:17.750 --> 20:20.549
Al, do you know
what she does for me?

20:20.653 --> 20:22.246
Rosa?

20:22.355 --> 20:23.754
From my parish?

20:23.856 --> 20:25.346
What?

20:25.458 --> 20:29.452
She puts chocolate, hot fudge,

20:29.562 --> 20:31.496
and butterscotch

20:31.597 --> 20:32.962
on my sundaes.

20:33.065 --> 20:34.226
(chuckles)

20:34.333 --> 20:35.459
That's nice.

20:44.944 --> 20:46.776
Well, how was Hollywood?

20:46.879 --> 20:47.903
Did you have fun?

20:48.014 --> 20:49.072
Was it exciting?

20:49.182 --> 20:50.172
Oh, you should've been there.

20:50.283 --> 20:51.773
Fonzie almost killed himself.

20:51.884 --> 20:54.080
Yeah, I'll tell you,
those-those Hollywood chicks

20:54.187 --> 20:55.882
are something, you know?

20:55.988 --> 20:57.956
Fonz, I think she's talking
about the shark, you know...

20:58.057 --> 20:59.252
Oh, yeah.

20:59.358 --> 21:00.757
Sharks? Girls?

21:00.860 --> 21:02.191
I'll tell you later.

21:02.295 --> 21:05.856
Chachi, oh, we have
a nice little souvenir for you.

21:05.965 --> 21:07.194
- Joanie?
- Oh.

21:07.300 --> 21:09.394
Joanie, just what
I always wanted.

21:09.502 --> 21:11.493
Uh, not me, squirt-- this.

21:14.373 --> 21:15.841
Hey, that's great.

21:15.942 --> 21:18.001
Thanks, everybody.

21:18.110 --> 21:20.078
Especially you, blue eyes.

21:20.179 --> 21:21.977
Put your lips in neutral.

21:23.683 --> 21:26.778
Now, you been taking care
of business since I was gone?

21:26.886 --> 21:28.411
Oh, yeah, I did real good, Fonz.

21:28.521 --> 21:29.955
Eight new phone numbers.

21:31.591 --> 21:34.322
All right, Jane and Joan,
the twins-- hey.

21:34.427 --> 21:36.896
Millie, Beatrice...

21:36.996 --> 21:38.464
Beatrice.

21:38.564 --> 21:40.464
L-I promised to take her
to Hollywood.

21:40.566 --> 21:41.692
I forgot.

21:41.801 --> 21:44.065
Well, I'll let her ride my bike.

21:44.170 --> 21:46.229
I better go call her;
I'll see you later.

21:46.339 --> 21:47.397
- Bye.
- Bye, Fonz.

21:47.506 --> 21:49.065
Now, Chachi,
I hope that sweatshirt

21:49.175 --> 21:50.540
is the right size.

21:50.643 --> 21:53.135
Oh, it'll look great
once I cut off the sleeves.

21:53.246 --> 21:54.407
Well, thanks everybody.

21:54.513 --> 21:55.947
- See you.
- Bye.

21:56.048 --> 21:57.516
AL:
Wah, wah, wah.

21:57.617 --> 21:59.210
(chuckles)

21:59.318 --> 22:00.444
Hey, you know...
(chuckles)

22:00.553 --> 22:02.282
a Hollywood sweatshirt,

22:02.388 --> 22:04.482
all the way from California,
that's nice.

22:04.590 --> 22:06.149
- Yeah.
- For Chachi.

22:06.259 --> 22:09.456
It's good when you have friends
who-who bring presents.

22:09.562 --> 22:12.054
Especially when you don't
go anywhere yourself.

22:12.164 --> 22:13.928
It's-it's so nice
when they do that.

22:14.033 --> 22:16.900
Dad, maybe you should give it
to him before the man cries.

22:17.003 --> 22:17.993
All right.

22:19.105 --> 22:20.402
Here you are.

22:20.506 --> 22:22.304
This is from all of us, Al.

22:22.408 --> 22:23.398
Oh.

22:24.710 --> 22:25.472
"Hollywood."

22:25.578 --> 22:26.568
RICHIE: Yeah.

22:26.679 --> 22:28.078
You can hear the ocean in there.

22:31.918 --> 22:34.580
(everyone laughing)

22:34.687 --> 22:36.655
Hey, hey, Al,

22:36.756 --> 22:38.485
here's the thing you wanted
Ralph and me to get.

22:38.591 --> 22:39.922
Oh, uh, thanks, Potsie.

22:40.026 --> 22:41.084
- Listen, was Hollywood really...
- Hey,

22:41.193 --> 22:42.888
Al, come on, put it on.

22:42.995 --> 22:44.190
- Later, eh?
- Aw.

22:44.297 --> 22:45.765
Did you see any movie stars
when you were...

22:45.865 --> 22:47.196
Come on, Al,
what do you mean, "Later"?

22:47.300 --> 22:48.461
We carried it all the way
from California.

22:48.567 --> 22:49.591
- Yeah, come on, Al.
- Yeah, Al.

22:49.702 --> 22:51.136
- Come on, Al, please?
- Put it on.

22:51.237 --> 22:53.831
- Put it on.
- Come on, Al-- here.

22:53.940 --> 22:55.499
- Let me see it.
- What did you get?

22:55.608 --> 22:56.700
- You'll see, you'll see.
- What is it?

22:56.809 --> 22:57.776
- Wait a minute.
- It's great, it's great.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.003
- You know what it is?
- All right...

22:59.111 --> 23:00.340
all right, all right, all right.

23:05.651 --> 23:07.176
Hi, boys and girls.

23:07.286 --> 23:08.776
What do you think?

23:08.888 --> 23:10.378
Oh, it's you, Al,
definitely you.

23:10.489 --> 23:12.048
I gotta go. Come on.

23:12.158 --> 23:13.592
- Come on, Pots.
- Okay.

23:13.693 --> 23:15.320
Wait a minute!

23:15.428 --> 23:17.658
How am I gonna tell my mom
about busting her ironing board?

23:17.763 --> 23:20.095
How am I gonna tell my father
I'm back?

23:21.500 --> 23:23.025
- So long, friend.
- Well, it was nice.

23:23.135 --> 23:24.330
- Hey, thanks everybody.
- See you later, Al.

23:24.437 --> 23:26.633
- Thank you; it's so nice.
- Glad you liked it.

23:26.739 --> 23:28.833
I'm-I'm-I'm
so happy with all this.

23:28.941 --> 23:30.773
- Yeah.
- This is so much fun.

23:30.876 --> 23:33.311
Friends... (sniffling)

23:33.412 --> 23:36.541
Is it true, though,
what they say about Hollywood?

23:36.649 --> 23:38.583
Oh, yeah, it's amazing.

23:38.684 --> 23:40.174
Boy, you wouldn't believe...

23:40.286 --> 23:43.654
They put lettuce and tomatoes
on hamburgers, huh?

23:43.756 --> 23:46.282
Yeah, yeah, that glamorous.

23:46.392 --> 23:47.587
- Boy...!
- And sometimes...

23:47.693 --> 23:48.785
Yeah?

23:48.894 --> 23:50.055
...EVEI1 mayonnaise.

23:53.733 --> 23:55.462
Oh! Fonzie, we're leaving!

23:55.568 --> 23:57.764
Turn off the lights
and lock the place, will you?

23:57.870 --> 23:58.928
Mayonnaise?

23:59.038 --> 24:01.029
(singing quietly)

24:15.421 --> 24:17.412
(sighs)

24:22.261 --> 24:23.751
Heyyy.

24:23.863 --> 24:27.663
